node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Linnea on August 29, 2021. May be art.

node.text:
Lava girl! This piece probably needs some more refinement, but I’m really tired of working on it😭 maybe I’ll pick it back up in a week or so! That raised hand is looking kinda whack tbh, yikes. 

How long do you guys spend on your drawings on average? For me, I usually take about 2-3 days to work on full illustrations, if it takes longer then that I get bored and unmotivated. I wish I had the patience to create things that took longer, but alas, I am not  gifted with high concentration

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Linnea on August 27, 2021. May be an illustration of cloud.

node.text:
Oh, to sit on a ledge wrapped in a fluffy blanket made out of clouds☁️ Also made a version where it’s just a girl sitting on a ledge🤷‍♀️ I think it’s interesting how tweaking reality in a simple way can make for a more compelling storytelling narrative, so I wanted to make a “normal” version to draw comparison with. 

Third piece of my “elemental blanket” series! I’m making one with lava next, and then I guess I’m done? How many more natural elements are there that would make suitable blankets… if you have any suggestions, let me know!

node.text:
The newest action series that has swept the nation, featuring beloved characters such as cat, dog and mouse! What will our Hero do next as she faces her greatest challenge yet, and will she be able to save those she loves before time runs out? Tune in to find out!

For some reason I just really wanted to draw a comic character introduction page, despite never having written a comic? So I just made one up🙈 The narrative of these characters doesn’t exist outside this single image, unless you make up one of your own👁

node.text:
Another medical chart! the plan is to make a little zine out of them (which will be available as a preorder bonus for when I release my art book ;)

It’s going to be like a small medicinal information booklet, but instead of boring actual diseases it’ll be fictional ones like vampirism and supernatural ailments.

On another note, this is my third post in a row featuring a rib cage.. I feel like I’m overdoing it, but I just. Can’t. Stop!!
